The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Jaisalmer, Dec. 28 (PTI): Two jawans were killed and two injured in an explosion at a firing range 45km from Jaisalmer.           
	The blast took place while air force ammunition brought from Gujarat was being unloaded from a truck, the defence public relations officer, Lt Col N.N. Josh, said. The ammunition was meant for use at the Chandan firing range.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The directorate-general of civil aviation will investigate how the windshield of an Air India plane was damaged while it was taxiing for take-off from Delhi airport on Sunday evening.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): A mock anti-terror drill by police at a mall in Goregaon on Monday triggered panic in the neighbourhood. The exercise caused chaos as it coincided with Muharram. Armed with AK-47s and arriving in combat vehicles, about 250 policemen including quick response teams took position inside and outside Oberoi Mall in the Dindoshi area and carried out the exercise for about two hours.                   
	 Noida (PTI): Twenty employees of a call centre were injured when their bus collided with a truck on Monday morning around 6.30am at Sector 57 in Noida. After hitting the truck, the bus ran over a divider. The driver cited fog as the reason behind the collision.                   
	 Chennai (PTI): The Election Commission has postponed the Tamil Nadu Assembly bypolls from January 20 after opposition parties protested that the date coincided with the Pongal festival. The ruling DMK and its ally Congress had opposed the postponement of the elections.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Indo-Tibetan Border Police, which guards the China border, will create an elite para-gliding squad. A group of personnel is undergoing specialised training at a centre in Himachal Pradesh.                                                                                                                                              
